headline: Analog Devices (ADI): Exploring Valuation After Tech Sell-Off Sparks AI Profitability Concerns
summary: Analog Devices (ADI) shares slipped in the wake of a sector-wide tech sell-off, as Oracle's disappointing cloud margins raised new questions about the profitability of artificial intelligence. This broader market reaction overshadowed ADI's own positive business outlook. See our latest analysis for Analog Devices. Despite a turbulent trading session driven by sector jitters, Analog Devices' share price has still notched a 12.6% gain year-to-date. Its one-year total shareholder return stands...
